post_text:
Good evening Premier Family,

As you all know starting tomorrow, Tuesday, September 8th, our school doors will be open and we will begin incorporating our blended learning schedule. For all of you who signed your kiddos up for blended learning will be able to drop your child off tomorrow morning at 8:00 am. Please be mindful of our temperature check protocol, which will take place daily for our students, staff, and parents who enter the building. And one last friendly reminder, tomorrow all students who were assigned to Pod B will learn in the classroom and Pod A students and remote only students will continue to utilize Google Classroom. If you have any questions please feel free to contact your student's teacher by utilizing Class Dojo or contact the main office at 717 -234- 3200. Thank you!

post_text:
Good morning,

Today at 8:40 a.m. begins the 2020 and 2021 school year for Premier Arts and Science Charter School, remotely, and our administrative team thought that this friendly reminder would be beneficial. Please log your student on to the Google Classroom platform at 8:40 am and please make sure that they are comfortably sitting at a table or desk while instruction takes place.

Students must also be fully dressed in appropriate attire and our school uniform is not required but is encouraged. If you have any questions, please contact us at 717-234-3200 and a member of our staff will gladly assist you. Thank you for your patience and remember being fearless requires excellence and excellence is a habit, not an act!

#PASCS

post_text:
Good morning Premier family,

It is extremely important that our students have access to a world class education, especially during this unprecedented time. As we prepare for the 2020 - 2021 School Year we will be incorporating both a blended and remote learning option, to secure safety for our students.

Today, starting at 9:30 am to 11:30 am, parents and guardians who requested a Chromebook for your kindergarten or first grade student may pick your designated Chromebook from our school site.

All parents and guardians who requested a Chromebook for your child who are in 2nd or 3rd Grade may pick your designated Chromebook from our school site between the hours of 11:45 am and 12:30 pm.

And all parents who requested a Chromebook for your child who are in 4th or 5th Grade may pick your designated Chromebook from our school site between the hours of 1:00 pm and 2:45 pm.

We can not wait to see your familiar faces 😀

post_text:
♟

Our administration, teachers, and parents push our students to pursue excellence with everything that they do at PASCS. Chess Club happens to be one of those enticing yet challenging activities that helps our students build life skills that they can implement not only on the chessboard but also in the classroom. This year’s Chess Club had over twenty-six students, and although Chess Club came to an immediate stop due to COVID - 19, all of our participants are winners and have exceeded our expectations. Thank you all for your interest and dedication during the 2019 - 2020 school year, and please remember this Premier Fun Fact; in life, take your time and make every move count.

#PASCS

Dear PASCS Family,

Mrs. Hudson and Mr. Marshall who are two of our Third Grade teachers and paraprofessionals would like to recognize one of their kiddos and that student is Angelica.

Angelica has been putting forward her best effort as a student during this unprecedented time. She has not missed one day and is constantly showing up on time. Angelica has also kept up with all of her online assignments. She has embraced our new distance learning routine and continues to strive every day.

Congratulations Angelica for being May 11th through May 17th Student of the Week!

We Are Premier Arts and Science Charter School Where Excellence Is A Habit Not An Act!

Dear PASCS Family,

Ms. McMichael, who is one of our Second Grade Teacher's would like to recognize one of her kiddos and that student is London.

London has had perfect attendance since the online classes began on 4/21/20. He has turned in all of his assignments and participates by reading, and asking and answering questions during class.

Ms. McMichael would also like to give a shout out to his mom, grandma, and aunt who have been there supporting him during class and asking me questions on class dojo if they need more information.

He has also won the gold trophy on Prodigy for having the highest percent of questions and having the right answers.

Thank you to all of you!!
London, YOU ROCK!!!!!!

Miss McMichael

post_text:
Dear parents and guardians,

On Tuesday, March 24th, and Friday, March 27th, the Harrisburg School District will have Grab-and-Go breakfast and lunch meals available for residents between the hours of 11:00 am to 12:30 pm. Also, on Tuesday, March 24th, and Friday, March 27th, family food boxes, donated by the Central Pennsylvania Food Bank are available on a first-come, first-served basis between 4:00 pm and 6:00 pm.

Families who attend Premier Arts and Science Charter School are also able to receive meals and food box pick-ups at one of the locations listed:

Foose School, Rowland Academy, John Harris Campus, Downey School, Ben Franklin School, and Cougar Academy.

Family participation is appreciated. Thank you, and please remain safe.

#PASCS

post_text: In compliance with Governor Wolf's mandate, all K through 12 Pennsylvania schools will be closed for ten business days, effective March 16th. This means that Premier Arts and Science Charter School will be closed now through March 27, 2020. Instructional packets will be provided for pick up for Premier's Kindergarten through Fifth grade students on Tuesday, March 17th between the hours of 8:00 a.m. and 4:00 p.m. Please be on the lookout for additional information and updates. Thank you.

post_text: Good afternoon. The administration at Premier Arts and Science Charter School would like to send out a friendly reminder about our school dismissal procedure. As our staff continues to put our student's safety first, please be mindful that dismissal is at 3:30 p.m. and no earlier than 3:15 p.m. Students who are pick-ups must be picked up at the front entrance only. Students who ride a day-care van will be dismissed no earlier than 3:15 p.m. and students who walk are dismissed no earlier than 3:30 p.m. If you have any questions please contact our main office. Thank you and enjoy your weekend!

post_text: In an extremely close race the members of the first student council for Premier Arts and Science Charter School have been chosen. We would like to congratulate Dasani Miles for being voted in for Class President. We would also like to congratulate Joshua Berry for being selected to be Vice President, Dwayne Marshall Jr., for receiving the Class Representative seat, and Phaedra Lucas for receiving the Student Treasure seat. This Thursday, we will have a small swear-in ceremony for our winners. Parents and guardians are invited.

post_text:
Early education is much more than just guaranteeing students the rights to learn how to read, write, and to do arithmetic efficiently, but it is also allowing students the ability to blend those subjects and be productive communicators as well as excellent leaders. Premier Arts and Science Charter School is having it's first-ever Fifth Grade Student Government, which will include campaigning, debating, and voting. Let's take some time to congratulate these students on having the courage to run and win!

Tentative schedule:

Dec. 4th, 2019 Q & A during 5th-Grade Lunch.

Dec. 4th through the 12th of 2019 candidates will campaign at school.

Dec. 13 is Election Day!

Seats that will be filled are President, Vice President, and Class Treasurer!

Premier Arts and Science Charter School is participating in a nationwide program to reduce illness over the flu and cold season by providing each family with a free digital thermometer and reminders on reducing the spread of germs. On October 11th, your child was given a flyer to bring home, outlining the program and instructions on how to participate and get your thermometer.

This program has a deadline which is October 31. Once you enroll and order your thermometer, your thermometer will then be delivered to the school and sent home with your child. If you have any questions please contact, Sue Saintz, the school Nurse, via email; ssaintz@pascs.org.

Thank you in advance for joining our efforts to reduce the spread of germs.

Premier Fact of the Day: What is the purpose of Title 1 Funding? "The purpose of this title is to ensure that all children have a fair, equal, and significant opportunity to obtain a high-quality education and reach, at a minimum, proficiency on challenging State academic achievement standards and state academic assessments" (U.S. Department of Education).

We hope to see as many parents and guardians tomorrow evening October, 16th, at 5:30 p.m. for our Title 1 Meeting. Refreshments will also be served! #PASCS

post_text: Thank you for visiting!
shared_text:
PA Charter Schools
March 14, 2019 at 4:14 PM ·

This morning we visited Premier Arts and Science Charter School in Harrisburg! PASCS began as a child care center and daycare where parents, students and the staff of Premier Learning Center, loved what the center was doing so much that they worked to continue that mission by founding a K-5 charter school! The original child care center is still operating just across the street from the school!

PASCS provides learning opportunities for students using a back-to-basics, phonics-centered approach to learning. With an early introduction to a second language, the students will increase their listening ability, memory, creativity, and critical thinking. Their Socratic Method of teaching enables students to test the logic and soundness of an idea and begin to fearlessly explore the world around them.
